id: pm-zumn
title: "Built-in MCP actions are now extension-aware: pm_profile/pm_list/pm_schema activate workspace extensions like the CLI"
description: "cubic (PR #404) noted that MCP pm_profile lint (and show/apply) resolve only built-in profiles because runAction (src/mcp/server.ts) runs built-in native actions WITHOUT activating workspace extensions or setting the active registration registry — only the dynamic-extension-dispatch fallback (runDynamicExtensionAction) activates+sets registrations. So getActiveExtensionRegistrations() is empty for built-in actions, and extension-contributed profiles/item-types are invisible over MCP, while the CLI path (main.ts activates extensions for every command) IS extension-aware. This is a pre-existing, broad asymmetry affecting all built-in MCP actions that read extension registrations, not just profile. Fix: wrap built-in runAction dispatch in a load/activate/setActive.../teardown cycle (mirroring runDynamicExtensionActionExclusively) so MCP built-in actions see active extensions consistently with the CLI. Deferred from #404 (pm-j1fj); lint is consistent with show/apply today."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:mcp",living-map,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-06-29T20:28:26.280Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-30T06:10:43.169Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-5k4v
resolution: "Wrapped every native MCP action dispatch in a single resilient extension activation cycle (withActiveExtensions) so built-in actions see extension-contributed item types, fields, and profiles consistently with the CLI; unified the former dynamic-extension dispatch into the same cycle."
expected_result: "MCP built-in actions (pm_profile/pm_list/pm_schema/pm_create/...) resolve extension-contributed registrations exactly like the CLI, and a broken extension can never break a built-in action."
actual_result: "src/mcp/server.ts now loads/activates/publishes/tears down extensions per request via withActiveExtensions + withActiveExtensionsExclusively, with load/activate failures swallowed (CLI loadRuntimeExtensionSnapshot parity) so built-ins stay resilient; pm_profile list/show/lint over MCP now surface an extension-registered profile end to end (verified by integration test + manual stdio smoke); 100% coverage retained (262 files / 5257 tests)."
