  pm-fq80,related,"2026-06-30T05:32:42.373Z",null,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-30T05:32:57.262Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation evidence: runAction now delegates to withActiveExtensions(global, dispatchAction); the former runDynamicExtensionAction/runDynamicExtensionActionExclusively pair was replaced by withActiveExtensions (skips activation for the --no-extensions flag and missing-workspace paths, runs `init` etc. without a workspace), withActiveExtensionsExclusively (serialized load/activate/publish/run/clear/deactivate, load/activate failures swallowed to a null active runtime — CLI loadRuntimeExtensionSnapshot parity), and dispatchActiveExtensionAction (resolves dynamic actions against the already-published registries). The pm-bl6m concurrency serialization (extensionActivationQueue) now protects built-in actions too. Verified: full coverage node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage 262 files / 5257 tests 100% stmts/branches/funcs/lines; pnpm lint; pnpm typecheck; pnpm contracts:check current. Manual stdio smoke in an isolated temp workspace: a hand-placed schema-capability extension that calls api.registerProfile now resolves over MCP via pm_profile list (agile/ops/research + flow(extension)), pm_profile show flow (types [Card]), and pm_profile lint flow (ok); pm_create/pm_list/pm_health all intact; --no-extensions and broken-extension paths keep built-in pm_list working."
files[3]{path,scope,note}:
  src/mcp/server.ts,project,withActiveExtensions/withActiveExtensionsExclusively/dispatchActiveExtensionAction unify the activation cycle for all native actions
  tests/integration/profile-command.integration.spec.ts,project,end-to-end pm_profile list/show/lint over MCP surfaces an extension-registered profile
  tests/unit/mcp/mcp-server-branch-residual.spec.ts,project,"unit coverage for the activation cycle, resilient activation-failure fallback, and noExtensions/missing-workspace skip paths"
close_reason: "MCP built-in actions are now extension-aware via a unified, resilient activation cycle (withActiveExtensions); verified with full coverage, lint/typecheck/contracts, an end-to-end integration test, and a manual stdio smoke proving extension-contributed profiles resolve over MCP. Shipping in PR for feat/mcp-extension-aware-builtin-actions."
body: ""
